Lets look at the order of things.<br>
<br>
Your guild overruns my guild<br>
You hurt my feelings...<br>
I petition your obvious wrong doing<br>
Your guild gets a hand slap<br>
Your feelings are hurt.<br>
<br>
Dont break the rules and your feelings wont get hurt... <br>
<br>
I WILL contact GMs/Verant if you attempt to threaten my guild or myself with bullish tatics. I and the GMs/Verant seem to not approve. And if you dont want me to keep saying it, then stop breaking the rules. <br>
<br>
Ask yourself this, why do you think Frizz still comes when we call him to fear/trak/nextmobwehaveaproblemwith. I can tell you why, because he is concerned that rules will be broken that he is there to enforce. If he thought our guild to be the boy that cried wolf, would he come and hang out in the zone to make sure the rules that he sets are enforced? I think not. He comes because you have broken the rules before and might again. Someone has to be accountable for Conquests actions. <p><p align="center"><img src="http://www.world-net.net/users/twoslow/kaisen1.jpg">
